I've always had an intrest in pepakura/papercraft, but never the patience. especially for any of the small stuff like that. Pretty cool job Yukon! Idk if you remember, but there are some KSP papercraft plans [here](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/85044-FanWork-Fridays-KSP-Papercraft), and a BIG Kerbal model [here](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/69295-Creating-a-kerbal-papercraft-model)
I've seen those, but these don't rely on templates (I like freestyle)
All the more impressive. I like the cargobay on the shuttle in particular.

Rough edition of Tiangong 1

[![CIMG4655_zpsfslatuaa.jpg](http://i1383.photobucket.com/albums/ah315/Yukon0009/CIMG4655_zpsfslatuaa.jpg)](http://s1383.photobucket.com/user/Yukon0009/media/CIMG4655_zpsfslatuaa.jpg.html)

And a TF2 shotgun, because why not?

[![CIMG4657_zps4z4atigd.jpg](http://i1383.photobucket.com/albums/ah315/Yukon0009/CIMG4657_zps4z4atigd.jpg)](http://s1383.photobucket.com/user/Yukon0009/media/CIMG4657_zps4z4atigd.jpg.html)
Nice work! Especially love the Soyuz and Saturn V.

I've been building these for 3 years, so yeah, they have gotten a more refined.
